@*
    Optional Razor layout for consumers wiring the Bug-Fab viewer through MVC
    instead of the inline-HTML endpoints in `ViewerHtmlEndpoints.cs`.

    Default deployment: `BugFab.AspNetCore` ships its own self-contained HTML
    via Minimal API endpoints, so MVC view-rendering services are NOT required.
    These cshtml files exist for two cases:

    1. Consumers already running MVC who want to apply their own _Layout.cshtml
       (corporate header, custom navigation, theming).
    2. Consumers who want pixel-parity with the upstream Python reference's
       Jinja2 templates (`bug_fab/templates/_base.html`, `list.html`,
       `detail.html`) — port the markup verbatim into these files.

    Wire-up (consumer's Program.cs):

        builder.Services.AddRazorPages();
        // ... AddBugFab(...) ...

    Then call `app.MapBugFabApi()` to skip the inline HTML endpoints, and
    register your own `app.MapGet("/bug-fab/", ...)` returning a Razor view
    that uses these layouts.

    See the full upstream templates at:
    https://github.com/AZgeekster/Bug-Fab/tree/main/bug_fab/templates

    Path conventions in this layout:
    - `~/bug_fab/bug-fab.css` and `~/bug_fab/bug-fab.js` resolve against
      `wwwroot/bug_fab/`, the static-file directory the package vendors —
      this path is fixed and is NOT the same as `BugFabOptions.RoutePrefix`.
    - The home `<a href="...">` links to the host application's root, not
      the Bug-Fab mount. Use `@Url.RouteUrl("BugFab_HtmlList")` from a
      child view if you want to link to the list root under any prefix.
    - Child views use `@Url.RouteUrl("BugFab_*", ...)` instead of hard-coded
      `~/bug-fab/` paths so the layout works under any mount prefix.
*@
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>@ViewBag.Title — Bug-Fab</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/bug_fab/bug-fab.css" />
</head>
<body>
    <header class="bug-fab-header">
        <h1><a href="@Url.Content("~/")">Bug-Fab</a></h1>
    </header>
    <main class="bug-fab-viewer">
        @RenderBody()
    </main>
    <script src="~/bug_fab/bug-fab.js" defer></script>
</body>
</html>
